---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import { site } from '@/config';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title={`Work — ${site.name}`}
  description="Examples of the kinds of work we can do by directing AI."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-12 pb-20">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-4">Work</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-10">
      Real client work and conceptual examples of the kinds of problems we help solve by directing AI.
    </p>

    <!-- Real Project -->
    <div class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8 mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Celio's Forge</h2>
        <a 
          href="https://celiosforge.com" 
          target="_blank" 
          rel="noopener" 
          class="text-sm text-[var(--accent)] hover:underline"
        >
          Live site →
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-1">Virtual Tabletop for Dungeons & Dragons 5th Edition</p>
      
      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mt-4">
        <p>
          A custom virtual tabletop built for running D&D 5e campaigns. 
          Features interactive battle maps, token management, real-time collaboration for players and GMs, 
          integrated dice rolling, and tools designed specifically around 5th edition workflows.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Built with:</strong> Modern web stack for smooth performance and low friction during sessions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-6">Example Engagements</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-8">These are conceptual scenarios showing the kinds of challenges we typically help with.</p>

      <!-- Example 1 -->
      <div class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Internal Operations Suite</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-1">Example: Manufacturing or field services business</p>
        
        <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mt-4">
          <p>
            A company currently relies on spreadsheets, email, and generic tools for job tracking, quoting, scheduling, and client communication.
            We would design and build a tailored set of connected tools that match their actual workflows.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Potential impact:</strong> Reduced administrative overhead, faster turnaround on quotes and jobs, and fewer dropped balls between teams.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Example 2 -->
      <div class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Accelerated Feature Development</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-1">Example: Growing SaaS or product company</p>
        
        <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mt-4">
          <p>
            An engineering team has a strong product vision but limited bandwidth to ship complex new features quickly.
            We would partner with them to handle significant portions of the architecture, implementation, and iteration using AI-directed development.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Potential impact:</strong> Major features delivered faster while maintaining (or improving) code quality and team velocity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Example 3 -->
      <div class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Client Intake &amp; Automated Reporting Platform</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-1">Example: Professional services firm (accounting, consulting, or legal support)</p>
        
        <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mt-4">
          <p>
            A growing firm spends significant time manually gathering client information, sending status updates, and compiling reports from multiple disconnected tools.
            We would build a lightweight, branded client portal with guided intake forms, automated progress reporting, and secure document exchange.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Potential impact:</strong> Faster client onboarding, fewer status update emails, and professional-looking reports generated with minimal ongoing effort.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Example 4 -->
      <div class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">E-commerce Operations Hub</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-1">Example: Small online retailer or direct-to-consumer brand</p>
        
        <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mt-4">
          <p>
            A growing brand uses Shopify plus several other tools for inventory, customer support, and marketing, but the data is fragmented and manual work is increasing.
            We would build a central dashboard that pulls key data from their existing tools and adds custom workflows for order exceptions, returns, and customer communication.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Potential impact:</strong> Less time spent in multiple dashboards, fewer errors on orders, and clearer visibility into what’s actually happening in the business.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Example 5 -->
      <div class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Membership &amp; Community Platform</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-1">Example: Small membership organization, studio, or community group</p>
        
        <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mt-4">
          <p>
            An organization runs events, manages members, and shares resources, but relies on a mix of email lists, spreadsheets, and third-party tools that don’t talk to each other.
            We would design and build a simple branded membership site with event registration, member directory, resource library, and automated renewal reminders.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Potential impact:</strong> A much more professional and cohesive experience for members, with significantly less manual coordination for the organizers.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] italic border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
        These are illustrative examples of the kinds of businesses and problems we help with. 
        Actual client engagements are handled on a case-by-case basis.
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
